Joe Root was run out for 182 in the first innings of the second Test in Grenada . 
  England batsman was left stranded after James Anderson failed to run his bat into the wicket . 
  Root threw down his helmet and gloves after the error by the West Indies bowler . 
  He was denied the chance of scoring a double century in the second innings . 
  Root scored 182 runs in England's first innings on day four . 
 